# Design System Rules

## Absolute Priority

The Design System is the single source of truth for every visual decision. **Branding and institutional identity** are the same: everything that would change if the institute rebrands (name, legal name, tagline, logos, favicon, contact blocks, social links, palette, fonts) MUST be driven from `system.properties`, not duplicated in code.

## Branding & `system.properties` (non-negotiable)

1. **Single source of truth.** The file `system.properties` at the project root owns:
   - Identity: `app.name`, `app.legal.name`, `app.tagline`, `app.logo.path`, `app.logo.alt`, `app.favicon.path`
   - Visual tokens: colors, fonts, layout tokens (already listed there)
   - Global public info: contact email/phone/address, social URLs
2. **How it reaches the app.** Values are read via `src/lib/theme/themeParser.ts` (and related helpers), mirrored into CSS custom properties in `src/app/globals.css` (or generated theme), and/or exposed through a small server-only `getBrandConfig()` (or equivalent) consumed by layout and SEO metadata. Do not introduce a second “brand config” file unless it is generated from `system.properties`.
3. **Forbidden.** Hardcoding in `.tsx`, `.ts`, dictionaries (JSON), tests, or `layout` metadata:
   - Institute or product display names, legal names, or taglines as string literals (except tests that assert behavior on **mock** brand objects)
   - Paths or URLs to logos, favicon, or branded assets not derived from `system.properties` keys
   - Contact or social URLs that duplicate what belongs in `system.properties`
4. **i18n copy.** User-facing sentences stay in `src/dictionaries/*.json`, but **brand proper nouns and global slogans** that must stay aligned with legal/marketing SHOULD come from the same branding layer (e.g. props from config parsed from `system.properties`), not a second hardcoded string in every locale file. If a temporary literal exists during migration, it must match `app.name` / `app.tagline` in `system.properties` and be removed when the plumbing exists.
5. **New branding fields.** When product needs a new branded value (secondary logo, partner name, footer accreditation), add a key to `system.properties`, extend the parser/types if needed, then consume the token — never ship a one-off string in a component.

## Constraints

1. **No ad-hoc styles.** Every visual property (color, spacing, typography, shadow, border-radius) MUST reference a Design Token defined in the Tailwind theme or CSS custom properties sourced from `system.properties`.
2. **No hardcoded hex/rgb values.** Use semantic token names (`bg-primary`, `text-secondary`, etc.). If a new color is needed, add it to `system.properties` and the theme first.
3. **Atomic Design methodology.** Components live in three **shared** layers when behavior and layout are the same on every surface:
   - `src/components/atoms/` — Indivisible UI primitives shared across surfaces (Button, Input, Label, Badge).
   - `src/components/molecules/` — Shared compositions (FormField, shared field groups).
   - `src/components/organisms/` — Shared complex sections only when the **same** structure is used on web and PWA (rare); prefer surface-specific organisms below.
4. **Surface-specific design system (Desktop vs PWA).** The UI is **not** one responsive blob: desktop and installed PWA / mobile-native experiences MAY use different building blocks. Tokens and brand stay identical; **component trees differ** where UX requires it.
   - **`src/components/desktop/{atoms,molecules,organisms}/`** — Elements used **only** on the web-desktop surface (wide nav, hover menus, dense tables, multi-column chrome, pointer-first controls). Name exports clearly (e.g. `DesktopSidebar.tsx`, `DataTableToolbar.tsx`).
   - **`src/components/pwa/{atoms,molecules,organisms}/`** — Elements used **only** on mobile browser and/or **standalone PWA** (safe-area wrappers, bottom tab bars, full-width list rows, sheet-style actions, thumb-zone primary CTAs). Respect `env(safe-area-inset-*)` and min touch targets (see `05-pwa-mobile-native.mdc`).
   - **Shared vs fork rule:** If a control is literally the same on all surfaces, it stays under `atoms/` or `molecules/`. If it diverges in structure or affordances (not just CSS width), implement **desktop** and **pwa** variants in the corresponding surface folder; do not overload one component with endless `isPwa` props.
   - **Who renders which:** **Tier A** (student/parent-facing) screen entries use `useAppSurface()` / `SurfaceMountGate` to render **either** desktop **or** PWA, never both at once. **Tier B** (admin) may ship desktop-only; see `05-pwa-mobile-native.mdc`.
5. **Tailwind only.** Inline `style={}` is forbidden except for truly dynamic runtime values (e.g., user-uploaded image backgrounds). Prefer Tailwind classes via `className`. **Exception:** `padding`/`min-height` that incorporate `env(safe-area-inset-*)` may use inline `style` only in **PWA** layout shells when Tailwind arbitrary values are insufficient — keep those values limited to safe-area glue code.
6. **Reusability over convenience.** Before creating a new component, verify no existing shared atom/molecule or surface-specific counterpart already covers the need.

## Image file uploads (inline progress — canonical)

Any **user-visible** flow where the person selects an **image** (or image-containing bundle, e.g. favicon ZIP) and the app uploads or processes it MUST surface **inline progress** next to the control — not only a disabled button or a silent wait.

1. **Molecule.** Use **`InlineUploadProgressBar`** (`src/components/molecules/InlineUploadProgressBar.tsx`): semantic `<progress>`, tokens only, `aria-live="polite"` while active. Do not invent ad-hoc progress bars for image uploads.
2. **Two-phase model (default with server actions + base64).**
   - **Reading / preparing** — Determinate `value` (0–100) when the browser reads the `File` (e.g. **`readImageFileAsBase64`** with **`onProgress`** in `src/components/dashboard/admin/site-setup/readImageFileAsBase64.ts`).
   - **Sending / saving** — **Indeterminate** bar (`indeterminate`) while the server action or opaque network step runs (no byte-level progress available on that path).
3. **Copy.** Labels for those phases MUST come from **`src/dictionaries/en.json` + `es.json`** (reuse existing keys such as `dashboard.siteSetup.uploadProgress*` / `admin.cms.templates.editor.brandAssets.uploadProgress*` or add aligned keys under the feature namespace).
4. **KV / long jobs.** **`importJobKv`** and similar are for **multi-step server jobs** (e.g. bulk import), not the default for a single image field. Do not wire KV solely to fake progress on a normal image upload unless the flow is explicitly job-based per **`11-long-running-jobs-ui.mdc`**.
5. **True HTTP upload percentage.** When product requires **network upload** progress (large files, slow links), prefer **client upload to Storage via signed URL** with **`XMLHttpRequest` / `upload.onprogress`** (pattern aligned with `prepareGlobalContentFileUploadAction` + `uploadToSignedUrl`), then a short server action to finalize metadata — still pair with **`InlineUploadProgressBar`** for the UX shell.

**Agent / PR checklist:** New or substantially changed **image file** picker → wired **`InlineUploadProgressBar`** + dictionary-backed phase labels + tests or RTL smoke for the busy state when feasible (**`02-testing-tdd.mdc`**).

## Checklist de contribución (componente nuevo en el design system)

Al añadir un componente compartido o de superficie (`atoms` / `molecules` / `organisms` / `desktop` / `pwa`):

- [ ] **Tokens** — colores, radios, tipografía y espaciado solo vía tema / CSS vars de `system.properties` (`01`), sin hex sueltos.
- [ ] **Export** — **named export**, un componente principal por archivo (`03-architecture.mdc`).
- [ ] **Superficie** — carpeta correcta (compartido vs `desktop/` vs `pwa/`); Tier A detrás de `useAppSurface()` cuando aplique (`05-pwa-mobile-native.mdc`).
- [ ] **i18n** — copy visible desde diccionarios (`09-i18n-copy.mdc`); `aria-label` / `title` accionables igual.
- [ ] **Tests** — al menos **humo** o prueba de comportamiento con Testing Library en `src/__tests__/` para interacción o estados relevantes; regresiones visibles cubiertas.
- [ ] **Accesibilidad** — contraste y controles solo icono con etiqueta; sin depender solo de hover para acciones críticas (`05`).
- [ ] **Documentación** — en la PR: propósito, props principales y ejemplo de uso (si el repo añade Storybook u otra vitrina en el futuro, enlazar o duplicar ahí).

## Contrast (WCAG-minded)

1. **Text and icons** on any background must keep **readable contrast** (aim for **WCAG AA**: ~**4.5:1** for normal text, ~**3:1** for large text / **non-text UI** such as icon strokes on interactive controls).
2. **Destructive / error affordances** — Do **not** place `text-[var(--color-error)]` (or similar) on **same-hue saturated** surfaces (e.g. brand red `secondary` button): the icon and label fail contrast. Prefer **neutral surfaces** (`surface`, `muted`) with **`border-[var(--color-error)]`** and **`text-[var(--color-error)]`**, or **light-on-dark** using `secondary-foreground` on the brand red **only** when the whole control is that fill (single foreground color).

## Icon-only controls

1. If the visible UI is **only an icon** (no adjacent text), you **must** set **`aria-label`** with a clear action (same copy you would use for a visible label, or fuller wording from i18n).
2. **Ideally** also set **`title`** (native tooltip) with the same or complementary copy so pointer users get a hint on hover; for longer explanations, prefer dictionary keys used consistently for `aria-label` / `title`.
3. Decorative icons: **`aria-hidden`** and no duplicate `aria-label` on the SVG.
